{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":785,"text":"So I am a surgeon who studies creativity,"},{"time":3282,"text":"and I have never had a patient tell me,"},{"time":6134,"text":"\"I really want you\nto be creative during surgery,\""},{"time":9000,"text":"and so I guess\nthere's a little bit of irony to it."},{"time":12143,"text":"I will say though that,\nafter having done surgery a lot,"},{"time":15467,"text":"it's similar to playing\na musical instrument."},{"time":17701,"text":"And for me, this deep\nand enduring fascination with sound"},{"time":20555,"text":"is what led me to both be a surgeon"},{"time":22321,"text":"and to study the science\nof sound, particularly music."},{"time":24879,"text":"I'm going to talk\nover the next few minutes"},{"time":26952,"text":"about my career"},{"time":28267,"text":"in terms of how I'm able to study music"},{"time":30575,"text":"and try to grapple\nwith all these questions"},{"time":32633,"text":"of how the brain is able to be creative."},{"time":35000,"text":"I've done most of this work\nat Johns Hopkins University,"},{"time":37654,"text":"and at the National Institute\nof Health where I was previously."},{"time":40663,"text":"I'll go over some science experiments\nand cover three musical experiments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44194,"text":"I will start off by playing\na video for you."},{"time":46274,"text":"This video is of Keith Jarrett,\nwho's a well-known jazz improviser"},{"time":49401,"text":"and probably the most\nwell-known, iconic example"},{"time":51869,"text":"of someone who takes improvisation\nto a higher level."},{"time":54386,"text":"And he'll improvise entire concerts\noff the top of his head,"},{"time":57549,"text":"and he'll never play it\nexactly the same way again,"},{"time":59978,"text":"so as a form of intense creativity,"},{"time":61987,"text":"I think this is a great example."},{"time":63629,"text":"And so why don't we go\nand click the video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":121795,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123820,"text":"It's really a remarkable\nthing that happens there."},{"time":126183,"text":"I've always as a listener, as a fan,"},{"time":127935,"text":"I listen to that, and I'm astounded."},{"time":129676,"text":"I think -- how can this possibly be?"},{"time":131436,"text":"How can the brain generate\nthat much information,"},{"time":133751,"text":"that much music, spontaneously?"},{"time":135360,"text":"And so I set out\nwith this concept, scientifically,"},{"time":138000,"text":"that artistic creativity,\nit's magical, but it's not magic,"},{"time":142375,"text":"meaning that it's a product of the brain."},{"time":144406,"text":"There's not too many brain-dead\npeople creating art."},{"time":146864,"text":"With this notion that artistic creativity\nis in fact a neurologic product,"},{"time":150519,"text":"I took this thesis that we could study it"},{"time":153000,"text":"just like we study any other\ncomplex neurologic process,"},{"time":156138,"text":"and there are subquestions\nthat I put there."},{"time":158217,"text":"Is it possible to study\ncreativity scientifically?"},{"time":160627,"text":"And I think that's a good question."},{"time":162688,"text":"And I'll tell you that most\nscientific studies of music,"},{"time":165398,"text":"they're very dense,"},{"time":166940,"text":"and when you go through them,"},{"time":168359,"text":"it's very hard to recognize\nthe music in it."},{"time":170453,"text":"In fact, they seem to be\nunmusical entirely"},{"time":172696,"text":"and to miss the point of the music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174514,"text":"This brings the second question:"},{"time":176094,"text":"Why should scientists study creativity?"},{"time":178000,"text":"Maybe we're not the right people to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180103,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":181126,"text":"Well it may be, but I will say that,\nfrom a scientific perspective,"},{"time":184602,"text":"we talked a lot about innovation today,"},{"time":186644,"text":"the science of innovation,"},{"time":188000,"text":"how much we understand\nabout how the brain is able to innovate"},{"time":190977,"text":"is in its infancy,"},{"time":192245,"text":"and truly, we know very little\nabout how we are able to be creative."},{"time":195736,"text":"I think that we're going to see,"},{"time":197284,"text":"over the next 10, 20, 30 years,"},{"time":199000,"text":"a real science of creativity\nthat's burgeoning"},{"time":201195,"text":"and is going to flourish,"},{"time":202420,"text":"Because we now have new methods\nthat can enable us"},{"time":204876,"text":"to take this process\nlike complex jazz improvisation,"},{"time":207424,"text":"and study it rigorously."},{"time":208822,"text":"So it gets down to the brain."},{"time":210993,"text":"All of us have this remarkable brain,"},{"time":212811,"text":"which is poorly understood,\nto say the least."},{"time":215290,"text":"I think that neuroscientists\nhave more questions than answers,"},{"time":219512,"text":"and I'm not going\nto give you answers today,"},{"time":221738,"text":"just ask a lot of questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223123,"text":"And that's what I do in my lab."},{"time":224654,"text":"I ask questions about what is the brain\ndoing to enable us to do this."},{"time":227992,"text":"This is the main method that I use.\nThis is functional MRI."},{"time":230793,"text":"If you've been in an MRI scanner,\nit's very much the same,"},{"time":233540,"text":"but this one is outfitted in a special way\nto not just take pictures of your brain,"},{"time":237479,"text":"but to also take pictures\nof active areas of the brain."},{"time":240430,"text":"The way that's done is by the following:"},{"time":242359,"text":"There's something called BOLD imaging,"},{"time":244193,"text":"which is Blood Oxygen\nLevel Dependent imaging."},{"time":247281,"text":"When you're in an fMRI scanner,\nyou're in a big magnet"},{"time":249890,"text":"that's aligning your molecules\nin certain areas."},{"time":252287,"text":"When an area of the brain is active,\nmeaning a neural area is active,"},{"time":256030,"text":"it gets blood flow shunted to that area."},{"time":258292,"text":"That blood flow causes an increase\nin local blood to that area"},{"time":262666,"text":"with a deoxyhemoglobin\nchange in concentration."},{"time":265673,"text":"Deoxyhemoglobin can be detected by MRI,"},{"time":267852,"text":"whereas oxyhemoglobin can't."},{"time":269726,"text":"So through this method of inference --"},{"time":271704,"text":"and we're measuring blood flow,\nnot neural activity --"},{"time":274270,"text":"we say that an area of the brain\nthat's getting more blood"},{"time":277030,"text":"was active during a particular task,\nand that's the crux of how fMRI works."},{"time":280596,"text":"And it's been used since the '90s\nto study really complex processes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284525,"text":"I'm going to review a study that I did,\nwhich was jazz in an fMRI scanner."},{"time":288049,"text":"It was done with a colleague,\nAlan Braun, at the NIH."},{"time":290576,"text":"This is a short video\nof how we did this project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"(Video) Charles Limb: This is a plastic\nMIDI piano keyboard"},{"time":295805,"text":"that we use for the jazz experiments."},{"time":297610,"text":"And it's a 35-key keyboard"},{"time":299687,"text":"designed to fit both inside the scanner,"},{"time":302171,"text":"be magnetically safe,"},{"time":303531,"text":"have minimal interference\nthat would contribute to any artifact,"},{"time":307397,"text":"and have this cushion\nso that it can rest on the players' legs"},{"time":310341,"text":"while they're lying down in the scanner,\nplaying on their back."},{"time":313320,"text":"It works like this --\nthis doesn't actually produce any sound."},{"time":316373,"text":"It sends out what's called\na MIDI signal --"},{"time":318840,"text":"or a Musical Instrument\nDigital Interface --"},{"time":320913,"text":"through these wires into the box\nand then the computer,"},{"time":323598,"text":"which then trigger\nhigh-quality piano samples like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326557,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333049,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":352333,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354332,"text":"OK, so it works."},{"time":356000,"text":"And so through this piano keyboard,"},{"time":358000,"text":"we have the means to take\na musical process and study it."},{"time":360767,"text":"So what do you do now that you have\nthis cool piano keyboard?"},{"time":363718,"text":"You can't just say,\n\"It's great we have a keyboard.\""},{"time":366187,"text":"We have to come up\nwith a scientific experiment."},{"time":368535,"text":"The experiment\nreally rests on the following:"},{"time":370929,"text":"What happens in the brain during something\nthat's memorized and over-learned,"},{"time":374597,"text":"and what happens in the brain\nduring something"},{"time":376776,"text":"that is spontaneously\ngenerated, or improvised,"},{"time":379074,"text":"in a way that's matched motorically"},{"time":380912,"text":"and in terms of lower-level\nsensory motor features?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":383781,"text":"I have here what we call the paradigms."},{"time":386400,"text":"There's a scale paradigm, which is playing\na scale up and down, memorized,"},{"time":389920,"text":"then there's improvising on a scale,"},{"time":391678,"text":"quarter notes, metronome, right hand --"},{"time":393739,"text":"scientifically very safe,"},{"time":395334,"text":"but musically really boring."},{"time":397231,"text":"Then there's the bottom one,\nwhich is called the jazz paradigm."},{"time":400226,"text":"So we brought professional\njazz players to the NIH,"},{"time":402654,"text":"and we had them memorize\nthis piece of music on the lower-left,"},{"time":405631,"text":"which is what you heard me playing --"},{"time":407473,"text":"and we had them improvise\nto the same chord changes."},{"time":409990,"text":"And if you can hit\nthat lower-right sound icon,"},{"time":412222,"text":"that's an example\nof what was recorded in the scanner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415074,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":439804,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":441829,"text":"In the end, it's not the most\nnatural environment,"},{"time":444269,"text":"but they're able to play real music."},{"time":446199,"text":"And I've listened to that solo 200 times,"},{"time":448194,"text":"and I still like it."},{"time":449395,"text":"And the musicians\nwere comfortable in the end."},{"time":451806,"text":"We first measured the number of notes."},{"time":453654,"text":"Were they playing more notes\nwhen they were improvising?"},{"time":456335,"text":"That was not what was going on."},{"time":457949,"text":"And then we looked at the brain activity."},{"time":459958,"text":"I will try to condense this for you."},{"time":461790,"text":"These are contrast maps that are showing\nsubtractions between what changes"},{"time":465294,"text":"when you're improvising\nvs. when you're doing something memorized."},{"time":468414,"text":"In red is an area that's active\nin the prefrontal cortex,"},{"time":471223,"text":"the frontal lobe of the brain,"},{"time":472706,"text":"and in blue is this area\nthat was deactivated."},{"time":474909,"text":"So we had this focal area\ncalled the medial prefrontal cortex"},{"time":477809,"text":"that went way up in activity."},{"time":479220,"text":"We had this broad patch of area\ncalled the lateral prefrontal cortex"},{"time":482474,"text":"that went way down in activity,"},{"time":484023,"text":"I'll summarize that for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485535,"text":"These are multifunctional\nareas of the brain,"},{"time":487667,"text":"these are not the jazz areas of the brain."},{"time":489846,"text":"They do a whole host of things"},{"time":491798,"text":"that have to do with self-reflection,"},{"time":493681,"text":"introspection, working memory etc."},{"time":496065,"text":"Really, consciousness is seated\nin the frontal lobe."},{"time":498576,"text":"But we have this combination"},{"time":500634,"text":"of an area that's thought to be involved\nin self-monitoring, turning off,"},{"time":504107,"text":"and this area that's thought\nto be autobiographical,"},{"time":506594,"text":"or self-expressive, turning on."},{"time":508153,"text":"We think, at least in this preliminary --"},{"time":510248,"text":"it's one study; it's probably wrong,\nbut it's one study --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513025,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514088,"text":"we think that at least\na reasonable hypothesis"},{"time":516843,"text":"is that, to be creative,"},{"time":518028,"text":"you should have this weird dissociation\nin your frontal lobe."},{"time":520928,"text":"One area turns on,\nand a big area shuts off,"},{"time":523476,"text":"so that you're not inhibited,\nyou're willing to make mistakes,"},{"time":526438,"text":"so that you're not constantly\nshutting down"},{"time":528630,"text":"all of these new generative impulses."},{"time":530579,"text":"Now a lot of people know that music\nis not always a solo activity --"},{"time":534048,"text":"sometimes it's done communicatively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535792,"text":"The next question was:"},{"time":537000,"text":"What happens when musicians\nare trading back and forth,"},{"time":539596,"text":"something called \"trading fours,\""},{"time":541233,"text":"which is something they do\nnormally in a jazz experiment."},{"time":544080,"text":"So this is a 12-bar blues,"},{"time":545517,"text":"and I've broken it\ndown into four-bar groups,"},{"time":547650,"text":"so you would know how you would trade."},{"time":549486,"text":"We brought a musician\ninto the scanner, same way,"},{"time":551796,"text":"had them memorize this melody"},{"time":553232,"text":"then had another musician\nout in the control room"},{"time":555822,"text":"trading back and forth interactively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557815,"text":"So this is a musician, Mike Pope,"},{"time":560463,"text":"one of the world's best bassists\nand a fantastic piano player."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563573,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569856,"text":"He's now playing the piece\nthat we just saw"},{"time":572246,"text":"a little better than I wrote it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"(Video) CL: Mike, come on in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575790,"text":"Mike Pope: May the force be with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577584,"text":"Nurse: Nothing in your pockets, Mike?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":579374,"text":"MP: No. Nothing's in my pockets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590577,"text":"CL: You have to have the right\nattitude to agree to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593379,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":594659,"text":"It's kind of fun, actually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596498,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598121,"text":"Now we're playing back and forth."},{"time":599844,"text":"He's in there.\nYou can see his legs up there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602080,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603446,"text":"And then I'm in the control room here,\nplaying back and forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606660,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616130,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":618000,"text":"(Video) Mike Pope:\nThis is a pretty good representation"},{"time":621368,"text":"of what it's like."},{"time":623176,"text":"And it's good that it's not too quick."},{"time":625200,"text":"The fact that we do it over and over again"},{"time":627803,"text":"lets you acclimate to your surroundings."},{"time":632033,"text":"So the hardest thing for me\nwas the kinesthetic thing,"},{"time":634715,"text":"looking at my hands through two mirrors,"},{"time":638000,"text":"laying on my back,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and not able to move at all\nexcept for my hand."},{"time":642702,"text":"That was challenging."},{"time":644598,"text":"But again --"},{"time":646952,"text":"there were moments, for sure --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649762,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":650787,"text":"there were moments of real, honest-to-God\nmusical interplay, for sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655786,"text":"CL: At this point,\nI'll take a few moments."},{"time":657812,"text":"So what you're seeing here --"},{"time":659717,"text":"and I'm doing a cardinal sin in science,"},{"time":661818,"text":"which is to show you preliminary data."},{"time":663652,"text":"This is one subject's data."},{"time":665429,"text":"This is, in fact, Mike Pope's data."},{"time":667200,"text":"So what am I showing you here?"},{"time":668700,"text":"When he was trading fours with me,\nimprovising vs. memorized,"},{"time":672835,"text":"his language areas lit up,\nhis Broca's area,"},{"time":675608,"text":"in the inferior frontal gyrus on the left."},{"time":677694,"text":"He had it also homologous on the right."},{"time":679627,"text":"This is an area thought to be\ninvolved in expressive communication."},{"time":682810,"text":"This whole notion\nthat music is a language --"},{"time":684962,"text":"maybe there's a neurologic\nbasis to it after all,"},{"time":687285,"text":"and we can see it when two musicians\nare having a musical conversation."},{"time":690663,"text":"So we've done this on eight subjects now,"},{"time":692660,"text":"and we're getting all the data together,"},{"time":694613,"text":"hopefully we'll have something\nto say about it meaningfully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697462,"text":"Now when I think about improvisation\nand the language, what's next?"},{"time":700729,"text":"Rap, of course, rap -- freestyle."},{"time":703000,"text":"I've always been fascinated by freestyle."},{"time":705771,"text":"And let's play this video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707308,"text":"(Video) Mos Def: Brown skin I be,\nstanding five-ten I be"},{"time":710170,"text":"Rockin' it when I be, in your vicinity"},{"time":712216,"text":"Whole-style synergy, recognize symmetry"},{"time":715260,"text":"Go and try to injure me,\nbroke 'em down chemically"},{"time":717618,"text":"Ain't the number 10 MC,\ntalk about how been I be"},{"time":720071,"text":"Styled it like Kennedy,\nlate like a 10 to three"},{"time":722493,"text":"When I say when I be,\ngirls say bend that key cut"}]},{"cues":[{"time":725335,"text":"CL: So there's a lot of analogy"},{"time":727177,"text":"between what takes place\nin freestyle rap and jazz."},{"time":729657,"text":"There are a lot of correlates\nbetween the two forms of music,"},{"time":732598,"text":"I think, in different time periods,\nin lot of ways,"},{"time":735069,"text":"rap serves the same social function\nthat jazz used to serve."},{"time":737924,"text":"So how do you study rap scientifically?"},{"time":739841,"text":"And my colleagues think I'm crazy,\nbut I think it's very viable."},{"time":743000,"text":"This is what you do:"},{"time":744251,"text":"You have a freestyle artist come\nand memorize a rap"},{"time":747022,"text":"that you write for them,"},{"time":748267,"text":"that they've never heard before,\nand then you have them freestyle."},{"time":751723,"text":"So I told my lab members\nthat I would rap for TED,"},{"time":754165,"text":"and they said, \"No, you won't.\""},{"time":755831,"text":"And then I thought --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":757058,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":758398,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":764148,"text":"But here's the thing."},{"time":765452,"text":"With this big screen,\nyou can all rap with me. OK?"},{"time":768377,"text":"So what we had them do"},{"time":770245,"text":"was memorize this lower-left\nsound icon, please."},{"time":772865,"text":"This is the control condition.\nThis is what they memorized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775782,"text":"Computer: Memory, thump."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777839,"text":"CL: Thump of the beat in a known repeat"},{"time":780000,"text":"Rhythm and rhyme, they make me complete"},{"time":783000,"text":"The climb is sublime when I'm on the mic"},{"time":785120,"text":"Spittin' rhymes that hit you\nlike a lightning strike"}]},{"cues":[{"time":787700,"text":"Computer: Search."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788888,"text":"CL: I search for the truth\nin this eternal quest"},{"time":791256,"text":"My passion's not fashion,\nyou can see how I'm dressed"},{"time":794010,"text":"Psychopathic words in my head appear"},{"time":796000,"text":"Whisper these lyrics only I can hear"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798262,"text":"Computer: Art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799458,"text":"CL: The art of discovering\nand that which is hovering"},{"time":802112,"text":"Inside the mind of those unconfined"},{"time":804000,"text":"All of these words keep\npouring out like rain"},{"time":807000,"text":"I need a mad scientist to check my brain"}]},{"cues":[{"time":809759,"text":"Computer: Stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811090,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820270,"text":"I guarantee you\nthat will never happen again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822468,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":824433,"text":"So now, what's great\nabout these free-stylers,"},{"time":826645,"text":"they will get cued different words."},{"time":828531,"text":"They don't know what's coming,"},{"time":829999,"text":"but they'll hear something off the cuff."},{"time":831939,"text":"Go hit that right sound icon,"},{"time":833372,"text":"there will be cued three square words:\nlike, not and head."},{"time":836116,"text":"He doesn't know what's coming.\nComputer: Like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838294,"text":"Freestyler: I'm like some kind of"},{"time":840088,"text":"extraterrestrial, celestial scene"},{"time":842341,"text":"Back in the days, I used to sit\nin pyramids and meditate"}]},{"cues":[{"time":845202,"text":"With two microphones -- Computer: Head"},{"time":847399,"text":"hovering over my head"},{"time":848757,"text":"See if I could still listen,"},{"time":850144,"text":"spittin' off the sound"},{"time":851455,"text":"See what you grinning"},{"time":852664,"text":"I teach the children\nin the back of the classroom"},{"time":855113,"text":"About the message of apocalyptical"}]},{"cues":[{"time":857534,"text":"Computer: Not."},{"time":858718,"text":"Not really though,\n'cause I've got to keep it simple"},{"time":861370,"text":"instrumental"},{"time":863000,"text":"Detrimental playing Super Mario"},{"time":866000,"text":"boxes [unclear] hip hop"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869177,"text":"Computer: Stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870621,"text":"CL: It's an incredible\nthing that's taking place."},{"time":872956,"text":"It's doing something\nneurologically remarkable."},{"time":875206,"text":"Whether or not you like\nthe music is irrelevant."},{"time":877546,"text":"Creatively speaking,\nit's just a phenomenal thing."},{"time":879971,"text":"This is a short video\nof how we do this in a scanner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882511,"text":"[fMRI of Hip-Hop Rap]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":884050,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885210,"text":"(Video) CL: We're here with Emmanuel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887008,"text":"CL: That was recorded\nin the scanner, by the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":889338,"text":"(Video) CL: That's Emmanuel\nin the scanner."},{"time":892000,"text":"He's just memorized a rhyme for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895042,"text":"[Control Condition Memorized Verses]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897749,"text":"Emmanuel: Top of the beat with no repeat"},{"time":900000,"text":"Rhythm and rhyme make me complete"},{"time":903000,"text":"Climb is sublime when I'm on the mic"},{"time":906000,"text":"Spittin' rhymes that'll hit you\nlike a lightning strike"}]},{"cues":[{"time":908798,"text":"Computer: Search."},{"time":909980,"text":"I search for the truth\nin this eternal quest"},{"time":912264,"text":"I'm passing on fashion;\nyou can see how I'm dressed"}]},{"cues":[{"time":914864,"text":"CL: I'm going to stop that there;\nso what do we see in his brain?"},{"time":917951,"text":"This is four rappers' brains."},{"time":919633,"text":"And we do see language areas lighting up,"},{"time":921693,"text":"but then, eyes closed --"},{"time":923000,"text":"when you are freestyling vs. memorizing,"},{"time":926337,"text":"you've got major visual areas lighting up."},{"time":928515,"text":"You've got major cerebellar activity,\nwhich is involved in motor coordination."},{"time":932228,"text":"You have heightened brain activity\nwhen you're doing a comparable task,"},{"time":935608,"text":"when that one task is creative\nand the other task is memorized."},{"time":938590,"text":"It's very preliminary,\nbut I think it's kind of cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941398,"text":"To conclude, we've got\na lot of questions to ask,"},{"time":943730,"text":"and like I said, we'll ask questions\nhere, not answer them."},{"time":946659,"text":"But we want to get at the root\nof what is creative genius neurologically,"},{"time":950134,"text":"and I think, with these methods,\nwe're getting close."},{"time":952715,"text":"And I think, hopefully\nin the next 10, 20 years,"},{"time":955042,"text":"you'll see real, meaningful studies"},{"time":956963,"text":"that say science has to catch up to art,"},{"time":960000,"text":"and maybe we're starting now to get there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962412,"text":"Thank you for your time, I appreciate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964434,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}